  "body": "## Description\nManaging fleet mode at scale and in a highly performant manner may require an event bus to correctly and accurately ship trie logs from a parent to many children. For now we rely on RPC. We may need to implement something more robust as we move this feature towards production. \n\n### To-Do\n- [ ] Validate current RPC performance for trie log shipping (max RPS for trielog shipping on parent node) \n- [ ] Validate performance degradation on the parent node as number of children increases (especially on low block time networks like Linea) \n- [ ] Decision point about event streaming \n- [ ] Follow-on ticket for scope and implementation \n",
